I"ô<p>In default logic, an extension is the result of properly applying a series of defaults. Extensions are defined as <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/cognitive-dissonance-reduction-drive-influences-body-state">coherent sets of beliefs about the world, generated</a> through default reasoning. However, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/world-models-reflect-ideological-structures">real world models appear much more complex</a> than the expressivity of default logic allows.</p>
